				//Ancient Pyramid events
	addLang('pyramid.signA'      , "The <b>Ancient Pyramid</b> towers before you menacingly. That's right. We wrote it on a sign here just in case you didn't notice that huge big-ass pyramid right in front of you.");
	addLang('pyramid.signB'      , "You have reached the End of the World! ... Seriously though, you won't find the lost treasure of Zzzxyasquesdetl here. You must go <b>inside</b> the pyramid.")
	addLang('pyramid.signC'      , "To the right, you will find the riddle section of the pyramid. We advise you not go there because you are too stupid to succeed.");
	addLang('pyramid.signD'      , "To the left, you will find the battle section of the pyramid. We advise you not go there because you are too weak to succeed.");
	addLang('pyramid.signE'      , "Tremble before my might! Better yet, turn around and leave my pyramid alone! -Zzzxyasquesdetl");
	addLang('pyramid.signF'      , "You seem to have reached a dead end, puny pony! The great Zzzxyasquesdetl scores another victory!");

	addLang('pyramid.signG'      , "Clue 1: Choose carefully, because if you choose wrongly, you will die! Then, your soul shall be sent to hell. Following that, the demons will salt it, grab some beer and feast upon it. When they're done, your soul will be made unto pieces in the demons' stomaches and then thrown into the great sewers of hell. And those are really stinky so you really don't want to choose wrong.");
	addLang('pyramid.signH'      , "Clue 2: There are four options in the lower chamber: Alpha, Beta, Gamma and Delta. Should you choose an extreme, you will surely perish.");
	addLang('pyramid.signJ'      , "Clue 4: You already have all the information you need! Don't bother this sign again! -Zzzxyasquesdetl");

	addLang('pyramid.signI.1'      , "Clue 3: Assign the number 1 to Alpha, 2 to Beta etc. Then multiply the number of ponies in the main cast by the the number of the Ticket Master episode, then add to this the number 3, and divide by seven. The choice not corresponding to the resulting number will cause your death.");
	addLang('pyramid.signI.2'      , "Clue 3: Assign the number 1 to Alpha, 2 to Beta etc. Then multiply the number of butterflies on the most shy cutiemark by the the number of apples on the big cutiemark, then add to this the number 5, and divide by two. The choice not corresponding to the resulting number will cause your death.");
	addLang('pyramid.signI.3'      , "Clue 3: Assign the number 1 to Alpha, 2 to Beta etc. Then multiply the number of Trixie episodes by the number of windigoes and subtract five. The not choice corresponding to the resulting number will cause your death.");

	addLang('pyramid.signK'      , "To the west of this tile is the ALPHA choice. If it is a wrong answer, stepping into it will cause you to die.");
	addLang('pyramid.signL'      , "To the west of this tile is the BETA choice. If it is a wrong answer, stepping into it will cause you to die.");
	addLang('pyramid.signM'      , "To the west of this tile is the GAMMA choice. If it is a wrong answer, stepping into it will cause you to die.");
	addLang('pyramid.signN'      , "To the west of this tile is the DELTA choice. If it is a wrong answer, stepping into it will cause you to die.");

	addLang('pyramid.victoryTile', "You have found the lost treasure of Zzzxyasquesdetl and cleared an Ancient Pyramid of threats! You are a hero!");
	addLang('pyramid.poolName'   , "Answer Pool");
	addLang('pyramid.poolText'   , "Stepping into this pool might open the door for you.. or it might kill you.");
	addLang('pyramid.poolWrong'  , "You step into the pool. Nothing happens.. <br />..but when you try to move back, you feel that you can't do it. You can't even make a single step. Was it truly an incorrect answer?...");
	addLang('pyramid.poolRight'  , "You step into the pool. Nothing happens.. <br />You move back and hear some grumbling at the south-east.<br />Correct answer! You may be as wise as Celestia herself. Or not. Probably not. Silly filly.");
	
				//Frozen cavern text
	addLang('frozen_caverns.note.description', "A note lies here, stuck between the ice plates on the floor.");
	addLang('frozen_caverns.note.text'       , "Stop. Don't go any further. I'm the last one from the EQSP team sent to investigate and will try to make it back. The walls here will freeze you to death if you touch them. We've seen dogs and constructs. Fleethoof was swallowed by a mimic, nothing we could do. We've heard the dogs talking about bug enchanters that advise the Which King. He has a draining sword, can disappear from sight and trap others in an ice, beware. I've discarded some equipment here, look around. If I won't make it, tell Maud I love her rocks. L. R.");
	addLang('frozen_caverns.boss_confront'   , 'A tall and menacing figure, covered fully in black spiked armour stands before you. His glares at you for a moment and begins the laugh. "Oh, thou look like such a fine steed. I shall crush thee, raise thee, than make thee my mount for this campain!"');
	addLang('frozen_caverns.wall_appears'    , 'A sinister laughter is heard from somewhere down the caverns. "A mere beast could never defeat me if I were in full power! Pathetic! But no matter, I shall rule this world and thou shall spend the eternity trapped in ice!" You hear a loud cracking noise and notice new ice walls start to raise from the floor.');
	
				// Old castle text
	addLang('old_castle.sign.entrance.text'   , '<b>Castle F iendship.</b> <br> Danger! Hostile magical creatures and deadly traps! DO NOT ENTER, everything here wants to kill you.');
	addLang('old_castle.sign.library.text'    , 'Library. <br > Keep QUIET! Failure to return books on time will result in disciplinary action.');
	
	addLang('old_castle.history.1'   , "You read a book about the castle's history.<br>... Castle Friendship was built in order to stop the Gryphon Tyranny from raiding the Trotting Valley. This was one of the first joint projects of the Equestria Alliance and a place where ponies of all the races could work together...");
	addLang('old_castle.history.2'   , "You read a book about the castle's design: <br>... A cloud generator was set on the roof for the pegasi, the stables were home of earth ponies, and the magical wing was properly warded so that the unicorns were not disturbed by the energy flux surrounding the castle. A library was build for those off-duty... ");
	addLang('old_castle.history.3'   , 'You read a book about the everyday life in the castle: <br>... After the Cloudspeak Peace was signed, many of the soldier-ponies were discharged and left to settle, leaving only a small joint garrison commanded by a unicorn captain Bright Star. Every morning, three pegasi wings patrolled the forest...');
	addLang('old_castle.history.4'   , "You read a scroll about the recent events in the castle: <br>...The order is to hold the castle at all costs. The flux-reinforced magical barrier around the castle is currently the only thing preventing the Shadow's advance on the valley below. Our spears, our wings and our wards are strong and our hearts are even stronger! We will not fail!");
	
	addLang('old_castle.journal.description', 'A piece of a dusty, old parchment lays here');
	addLang('old_castle.journal.0'   , 'Year 117 PA, 20th Hooftober. Captain Bright Star, standing commander of castle Friendship. Today the sun was blocked by a shroud, as Castle Friendship was besiged by the Shadow Pony herself. She came arrogantly to the barrier and threatened us to surrender or face a fate worse that death. I faced her and refused.');
	addLang('old_castle.journal.1'   , "21th Hooftober. The Shadow Pony unleashed waves of armoured constructs on us that somehow could pass the outer barrier. Those who fell were raised as shadows on the spot and caused chaos in our ranks. We pushed them back, but I had to ward off some of the castle's aisles with more permanent barriers using the energy crystals. A flickering light was noticed around the barrier, as the beast tried to disrupt our defences.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.2'   , "22th Hooftober. Situation is stable. We still have a lot of power crystals and other supplies. Every enemy advance is cut by a ward, while earth ponies hold the lines and teams of pegasi down the shadows that make it through with lightning sticks. Everyone is silently praying for a dawn.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.3'   , "23th Hooftober. The shadows breached the areal defences and we lost our cloudbase. The winged ones retreated and took refuge in a castle with the rest of us and I've sealed the roof. It's getting colder without the sun, so we all sleep in groups now, cuddled together near the fireplaces.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.4'   , "24th Hooftober. Wards are being breached all the time as attacks come from multiple directions. We use secret passages to renew the wards and clear the breaches, but it's getting harder and harder to focus and respond in time.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.5'   , "25th Hooftober. Morale is of concern. We've lost one third of our force and another third are wounded. Yet I feel like we are being harassed, as if the shades retreat too easily, trying to distract us. Are we winning? I need to investigate what is happening outside, I have a bad feeling about this.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.6'   , "26th Hooftober. The shadows were only a distraction to keep us inside! I've seen Her use powerful shadow magic to close a circle around the castle under the cover of the darkness. She must had been doing this from the beginning of the siege. I could try a resonating counter-spell in the nexus by figuring out and countering every element of her elemental sequence in order, but I'm afraid there is little time for that. She is coming. Goddesses help us.")
	
	
	addLang('old_castle.journal.element.1' , "I've noticed traces of fire magic by the barrier. It is fortunate that the castle is well-protected from fire.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.element.2' , "A cold howling wind came and blowed for hours. Is the Shadow Pony trying to break our spirit?");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.element.3' , "The ground shook a few times today. Some pots fell and broke, but there seems to be little other damage.");
	addLang('old_castle.journal.element.4' , "A dense magical fog covered the grounds around the castle for three hours. Sight was limited and the pegasi had trouble flying with wet wings.");
	
	addLang('old_castle.sign.nexus.text'     , 'Magical nexus. <br /> DANGER! Powerful magical flows with potentually lethal discharge. Authorized personnel only. ');

	addLang('old_castle.nexus.core.desc'     , 'A magical hexagram is drawn on the floor. A heavy iron chain lays nearby, attached to the floor with one end. ');
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.core.desc.on'  , 'It now conjoins energy in the following order: ');
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.core.desc.off' , 'It glows fainly with resudial energy.');
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.core.reset'    , "You drop the free end of the chain at the side of the hexagram and drain the energy from the figure.");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.core.cast'     , "The hexagram has been drained of all energy.");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.A'     , "A round stone with a carving of ");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.0'     , "a blazing sun");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.1'     , "a flame");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.2'     , "a rainbow");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.3'     , "a mountain");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.4'     , "a wave");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.5'     , "a half-moon");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.textOn'   ,"You align the stone with one of the corners from the hexagram. The hexagram glimmers as it realigns its flow with new energy. ");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.textStuck',"You have already aligned this stone and now it is fused with the energy of the hexagram. You can drain the energy in the center of the hexagram to release it.");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.element.textSpent',"The stone looks useless now, after it had been discharged by the spell.");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.spell.good'       ,"As you finish aligning the stones, the flows of magic into the hexagram consolidate into bright golden glow that resonates with the dark aura of this place, forcibly pushing it away from the room and farther and farther into the castle. You stand in the glow, absorbing the counterspell's light for some time, as you hear a wail from the castle's hallways - the ancient shadow has felt the effects too.");
	addLang('old_castle.nexus.spell.evil'       ,"As you finish aligning the stones, the flows of magic into the hexagram consolidate into bright golden glow that resonates with the dark aura of this place and unites with it. You stand in the glow, absorbing the spell's power, and see your true shadow extending under your feet. You step inside it, reverting your essence upon itself and enter the twilight-space. You feel your darkness's empowering gentle touch, as opposed to the darkness around you.");
	
	
	addLang('old_castle.shadow.description'  ,"You may have found the source of the magical disturbance in the castle. This shadow looks much denser than the others and has a shape of a unicorn. You see an orange cord of energy leading to the room behind it, probably connecting it to a source of power.")
	addLang('old_castle.boss.description'    ,"This is something big. Sinister. Ancient. You struggle to even look at her shadow, the shadow of the Shadow Pony.");
	addLang('old_castle.boss.appearence.start'	, "The powerful shadow whispers as it dissipates -");
	addLang('old_castle.boss.appearence.body'     ,"Yes... Finally a decent vessel came and freed me. Unfortunately, you woke the Shadow Pony's true shadow and it now hunts after your body. You may have just enough time to charge a counter-spell in the nexus behind me. You need to counter the elements she used every day of the siege. Her spell began with a flash, so you should first use the darkness symbol - the Moon!. Hurry... " );
	addLang('old_castle.boss.appearence.corrupted'     ,"<br>No, wait. I sense that you carry enough darkness within to get to Her place. Listen, if you instead recreate her spell step-by-step, you can charge your shadow and fight her in her own realm instead of facing a projection here. Destroy that old hag for good, Go!" );
	addLang('old_castle.boss.appearence.end'	,"<br>You decide to write down the fell champion's words. ");
	addLang('old_castle.boss.appearence.note'	,"You left a note here. ");
	
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.goodSpellVictory' ,"<h1>The 15-minute Champion of Light and the 15-year Shadow Crusade.<h1/>");
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.goodSpellVictory'   ,"<div>Empowered by the counter-spell, you strike down the dark form and tear the fleeing shadow pieces apart, until they are no more. The counter-spell quietly dissipates and you return to your normal self. A ray of light shines through a crack in the wall. You hear the birds sing outside. The place has finally became a quiet old ruin, with it's story becoming history. After a few years, you start having nightmares where you flee from your own shadow. With time you grow old and begin to tell frightening stories to young fillies about this place. Three of them actually sneak into the castle and accidentally recreate that shadow spell, beginning the Shadow Crusade.</div>");
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.evilSpellVictory'  ,"<h1>I, For One, Welcome Our New Shadow %r Overlord.<h1/>");
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.evilSpellVictory'    ,"<div>OUT! You scream as you force every bit of weakened Shadow Pony's true form out of twilight-space and onto the cold stones of the castle. She is ancient, indeed. So ancient, that time immediately catches on to her physical body and withers it away, quickly turning her silver flesh and bone to dust. All her remaining power slips easily into your gasp and the shadows of the castle gather around you to heed your commands. You wonder what will you do next.</div>");
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE +'.noSpellVictory'    ,"<h1>Exterminate!<h1/>");
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE +'.noSpellVictory'      ,"<div>A powerful blow forces the Shadow Pony to withdraw, but something holds her in place. Confused, she notices that magical orange strands have grown from the castle floor and are now wrapping around her feet. She tries to force herself away, but you quickly bash her with everything you have got. It takes some time, but the dark form finally collapses as the strands start to burn into her. You hear a quiet voice. <br>- These are souls of the last ones, whom she could not reach. Today, we have held and stopped the Shadow Pony. Mission complete. By the power given to me as castle Friendship commander, I, Captain Bright Star, relieve this garrison from duty. Rest in peace. Long live the princess. <br>The strands burn away with the dark form, until only ashes remain. The castle is quiet once again.</div>");
	
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.regularDefeat'   ,"<h1>Scavenger meat.<h1/>");
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.regularDefeat'     ,"<div>You fall on the floor, suffering mortal wounds. Some monsters chew on your body, your stuff gets broken or taken away. You die a foolish, but pretty normal death, never knowing what mystery this castle holds.</div>");
	
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.goodSpellDefeat'   ,"<h1>It's ok to be dead.<h1/>");
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.goodSpellDefeat'     ,"<div>Despite your best effort, you had been struck down. The power of the old witch was too great. <br> With great pain, your spirit is forced outside the body and the Shadow Pony takes over it. You meet your own body's gaze. The choice is simple - Submit or vanish. <br> Without an alternative, you chose to join her army as a mindless shadow.</div>");
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.evilSpellDefeat'   ,'"<h1>Live" another day.<h1/>');
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.evilSpellDefeat'     ,"<div>You have surprised the witch by going after her into twilight-space, but she still manages to drink your power faster than you can inflict damage. You should have thought this through. You scream in desperation as the Shadow Pony laughs at your efforts<br>- Feeling anguish, my love? It's such a nice feeling. I might let you lead some of my shades if you submit now, so I can come back for more. What do you say? <br> You quickly agree before your spirit is completely drained out, becoming one of her lieutenants in the upcoming conflict.</div>");
	addLang('ending.header.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.noSpellDefeat'     ,"<h1>Keep calm and eat brains.<h1/>");
	addLang('ending.text.' + FIELD_OLD_CASTLE + '.noSpellDefeat'       ,"<div>Blood drops from your ears, as her last lunge at you almost exploded your head. The Shadow looks at you with pity.<br> - This body is too weak and useless for me. That old fool lost existence in order to trick me, so you will take his place and test the next vessel that comes. <br> Your knees bend and everything turns black. You regain consciousness as you hear somepony's mind-voice in your mind: <br> - Hm, what's written here? Castle F... fiendship? Danger, hostile magical creatures and blah blah. The place is just an old ruin left from an old war! Ready team? We're going to get rich today! <br> Your will is gone and your memory is blank. But you understand you must guard this passage and you stand there, waiting.</div>");
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
